				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I imagine another reason guides tend to gloss over it is that, since it involves setting up basically every register in the system, to fully understand it you more-or-less have to understand the whole system already. A full breakdown of exactly what the init code is doing isn't a great thing to start a guide off with if you just want to start with basics and build up from there.</div>

